Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.50,0:02:59.54,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,Once upon a time...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.50,0:03:11.58,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,A kind young man and\Na beautiful young woman
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.58,0:03:21.50,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,Were joined in love
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.08,0:03:34.58,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,Jean and Jeanne
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.16,0:03:43.41,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,Dancing in the sky of bliss
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.45,0:03:53.58,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,Smiled upon by God
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.50,0:04:06.37,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,Drunk on happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.12,0:04:41.58,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,Jean and Jeanne
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.62,0:04:47.41,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,Together forever
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.16,0:04:52.50,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,Smiled upon by God
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.50,0:04:56.91,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,Forever with each other...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.58,0:05:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,May they live happily ever after.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.12,0:05:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But our story is just beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.00,0:05:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Your highness,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.37,0:05:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,today your loyal subjects\NJean and Jeanne
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.70,0:05:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,were joined in holy matrimony.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.16,0:05:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Honoring tradition, Jean has come to make
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.00,0:05:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,an offering to show his gratitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.45,0:06:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Your highness, please accept this money\Nin exchange for Jeanne's hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.25,0:06:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We sold our milk cow to get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.00,0:06:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,How many milk cows?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.29,0:06:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,One. We have only one cow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.83,0:06:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten cows.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.12,0:06:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Your highness is ordering\Nyou to pay ten cows in tax!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.75,0:06:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What?! I beg you...\NWe're too poor to pay ten cows.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.79,0:06:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Your ladyship, have pity!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.79,0:06:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this child chaste?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.00,0:06:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I vow on my soul\Nthat it was a pure marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.45,0:06:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeanne has never done anything unseemly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.62,0:06:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Earnest and hard working,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.54,0:06:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the pride and joy of our village.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.70,0:07:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Child, do you love this man?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.66,0:07:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, your ladyship!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.62,0:07:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And you her?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.12,0:07:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.87,0:07:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen everyone, after milord has had his\Nturn, you're all entitled to this offering!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.79,0:09:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's forget what happened.\NOur life starts from this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.00,0:10:44.00,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,What is that flickering
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.08,0:10:51.58,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,In the pale mirror?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.70,0:10:57.04,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,Not tears,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.12,0:11:01.12,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,Not sighs,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.83,0:11:15.08,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,But tomorrow's vanished scraps.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.62,0:11:20.66,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,Or could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.62,0:11:36.79,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,A woman's leaden body.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.16,0:11:47.54,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,What is that howling
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.41,0:11:55.12,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,In the black sunset?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.33,0:12:00.37,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,Not the night wind,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.45,0:12:04.29,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,Not a crow,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.45,0:12:19.37,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,But a creaking hinge of rusted hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.54,0:12:23.79,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,Or could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.41,0:12:40.37,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,A woman's painful moan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.70,0:13:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.25,0:13:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Look how tired he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.79,0:13:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't wake him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.91,0:13:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you?\NWhere did you come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.79,0:13:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You called me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.33,0:13:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I did?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.12,0:13:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure I heard it...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.58,0:13:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Your soul was screaming,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.66,0:13:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,"I want power. Someone help me."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.62,0:13:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And also...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.29,0:13:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,"I'll give anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.91,0:13:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,if someone would save me...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.45,0:13:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,even my soul."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.29,0:13:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you the devil?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.29,0:13:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I am you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.62,0:13:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That tickles. Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.95,0:14:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to give you power.\NAs you wished.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.79,0:14:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,A tiny thing like you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.20,0:14:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It's your fault that I'm tiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.29,0:14:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,My fault?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.00,0:14:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.00,0:14:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I can become as big\Nand as strong as you want me to.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.50,0:14:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all up to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.00,0:14:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You're so funny!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.83,0:14:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You're laughing!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.58,0:14:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's good to finally\Nsee you happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.91,0:14:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.87,0:14:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.08,0:14:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,laughed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.12,0:14:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I'd never laugh again.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.29,0:15:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand you, Jeanne.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.45,0:15:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I've always been by your side.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.08,0:15:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I know everything about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.79,0:15:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you, I am you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.12,0:15:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.50,0:15:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you...?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.37,0:15:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Where'd you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.08,0:16:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You're doomed at this rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.12,0:16:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Pray all you want...\NJust look at your husband, Jean!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.50,0:16:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Earnest and hard working,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.41,0:16:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,he should be in his prime,\Nbut he's already breaking down.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.29,0:16:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll probably get sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.16,0:16:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably won't make it past the winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.75,0:16:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.75,0:17:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.62,0:17:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't need anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.12,0:17:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I just...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.08,0:17:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,want to save him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.87,0:17:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.25,0:17:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,help me save him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.12,0:17:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that's more like it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.25,0:17:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeanne went to town to sell her thread.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.00,0:17:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The town was starving again that year,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.41,0:17:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,but the lord still collected taxes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.62,0:17:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,People were crushed by despair\Nand too weak to cry out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.62,0:17:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The only one working was Jeanne.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.58,0:18:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The town.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.08,0:18:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeanne's thread sold for a good price.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.66,0:18:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,No one even wanted to haggle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.00,0:18:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeanne's husband Jean was\Nthe only one in the village
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.33,0:18:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,able to pay the lord's high taxes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.66,0:18:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Rumors started spreading that\NJeanne was possessed by the devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.00,0:18:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Delighted that Jean\Nhad payed all his taxes,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.16,0:18:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the lord appointed\NJean town tax collector.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.29,0:18:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Before only a poor peasant,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.54,0:18:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,now Jean was an official in a red hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.83,0:18:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeanne was happy for\Nher husband's success.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.79,0:19:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jeanne also noticed\Nthat the villagers had changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.29,0:19:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Now they bowed deeply,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.62,0:19:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and avoided crossing paths\Nwith Jean and Jeanne.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.08,0:19:51.20,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,The darkness is burning
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.45,0:20:02.12,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,The darkness is burning
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.04,0:20:18.20,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,The darkness invites and seduces me
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.08,0:20:27.00,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,Burning darkness
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.45,0:20:39.00,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,Deep into it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.20,0:20:47.00,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,Blazing hot...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.12,0:21:00.37,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,The darkness is burning...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.00,0:21:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.66,0:21:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you want from me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.08,0:21:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This is only the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.29,0:21:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, this was only the beginning\Nof Jeanne's suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.29,0:21:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,War broke out.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.75,0:22:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,War is expensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.29,0:22:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But winning meant more land.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.08,0:22:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm leaving for the front tomorrow,\Nand this is all you collected?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.00,0:22:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.58,0:22:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but tomorrow I promise...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.79,0:22:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Fool! It takes more than\Na few drops to turn a mill!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.79,0:22:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't get all the money in\Nthree days, I'll have you hanged!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.33,0:22:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But your highness... no one\Nhas any more money left!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.50,0:22:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Teach this man to listen to orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.29,0:22:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Make his body remember.\NChop off his left hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.37,0:24:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You called me?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.20,0:24:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I did...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.79,0:24:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.25,0:24:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you want power.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.45,0:24:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You're cruel.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.79,0:24:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You're mine now.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.29,0:24:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Your body, your soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.54,0:24:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Lies!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.58,0:24:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,My soul belongs to Jean
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.12,0:24:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.50,0:24:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You beautiful fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.62,0:25:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Still you resist me,\Neven when you're beneath the rod!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.91,0:25:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Your husband is on\Nthe road to perdition.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.45,0:25:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What will you do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.87,0:25:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You're mine already,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.12,0:25:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,but I want you to accept me\Nof your own free will.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.45,0:25:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I also want your heart and soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.25,0:25:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, he will...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.79,0:25:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,This flesh, this rotting flesh,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.08,0:25:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll give it to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.12,0:25:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,if it will save Jean.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.54,0:26:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But not my soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.16,0:26:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I will never give you my soul!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.62,0:26:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well then. Hang onto it\Nfor a bit longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.12,0:27:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What, Jeanne?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.45,0:28:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeanne put on her green dress
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.62,0:28:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and went straight into town.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.29,0:28:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Th say green is the color of power,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.50,0:28:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the color of the devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.20,0:28:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The greedy old moneylender
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.08,0:28:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,who had even refused\Nto lend money to the lord
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.00,0:28:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,took one look at Jeanne\Nand loosened his purse strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.12,0:29:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Later he grumbled,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.08,0:29:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,"That woman must be\Npossessed by the devil."
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.00,0:29:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Men love war in every age.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.66,0:29:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The lord marched off in splendid array\Nwith his soldiers and conscripted farmers.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.20,0:29:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Women are always the\Nones left behind to suffer.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.91,0:29:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The men were gone for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.79,0:29:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Several years passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.83,0:29:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeanne had become a moneylender
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.37,0:30:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and gained control of the town.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.87,0:30:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,People feared and revered Jeanne\Nmore than the lord's wife
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.79,0:30:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and obeyed her gladly.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.41,0:30:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is in charge of this land while\Nhis lordship is away?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.41,0:30:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Me or that woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.50,0:30:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.54,0:30:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.08,0:30:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right to be angry, milady...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.66,0:30:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But the war has been prolonged.\NWithout her help,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.33,0:30:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,even we wouldn't have enough to eat...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.54,0:30:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Silence!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.00,0:30:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That witch will pay for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.45,0:31:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,However, despite his newfound stature,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.70,0:31:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Jean spent his days drinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.70,0:31:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Suddenly, the lord\Nreturned from the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.12,0:31:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Women and men were overjoyed\Nto find each other again.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.08,0:31:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The Lady rarely left her castle\Nto avoid seeing Jeanne,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.79,0:31:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,but that day she went to the church\Non the plaza to greet her husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.04,0:31:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeanne was there, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.29,0:32:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never seen that woman before.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.62,0:32:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Milord, things have been turned\Nupside down while you were away.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.37,0:32:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.00,0:32:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That farmer bitch is in\Nleague with the devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.00,0:32:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The devil?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.79,0:32:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The villagers respect her\Nmore than anyone now.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.37,0:32:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,More than you, even.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.12,0:32:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this true?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.33,0:32:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.45,0:33:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Satanic fiend!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.12,0:34:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Jean! Open the door! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.62,0:34:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Help!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.12,0:34:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Jean!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.54,0:34:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So you... didn't kill her.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.00,0:34:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Even better.\NWe'll burn her alive at the stake!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.45,0:34:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the best medicine for\Nwitches in league with the devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.75,0:35:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Heresy must indeed be\Nnipped in the bud.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.83,0:35:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if we burn her body\Nwhile her soul belongs to Satan...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.04,0:35:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What will happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.12,0:35:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If we set her body aflame\Non the mountain of tinder
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.12,0:35:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,only for her soul to survive the flames\Nin its haughty pride,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.54,0:35:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,then, though her body had died,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.79,0:35:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan would live on in her soul
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.50,0:35:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and might spread like sparks\Nfrom a fire to those all around.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.87,0:35:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you suggest?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.12,0:35:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Milady, you must lock her\Ndeep in a dungeon
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.66,0:35:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and hold onto the keys.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.29,0:35:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Then scourge her body
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.83,0:35:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,until the light of God\Nshines into her soul
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.45,0:36:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and teaches her meekness.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.25,0:36:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well. I'll see to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.83,0:36:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring her to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.83,0:37:07.37,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,What is burning
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.29,0:37:16.00,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,In the dark judgement?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.62,0:37:20.79,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,Not grief,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.79,0:37:24.91,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,Not penitence,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.66,0:37:39.37,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,But the silhouette of one exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.33,0:37:44.37,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,Or could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.62,0:38:00.37,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,A woman's strong resentment.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.41,0:38:12.00,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,What awaits
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.29,0:38:19.79,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,In the pale march of time?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.08,0:38:24.29,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,Not a life,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.45,0:38:28.50,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,Not a grave,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.37,0:38:43.20,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,But the mirage of a dead heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.66,0:38:48.58,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,Or could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.62,0:39:05.37,Default_Italic,,0,0,0,,A woman's crimson blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.58,0:41:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So you've finally come,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.29,0:41:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,my beloved!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.04,0:41:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Spit on by all, and now\Nabandoned by your own husband!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.12,0:41:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How I've been waiting for this moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.08,0:41:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeanne, since the day you were\Nborn into this world,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.75,0:41:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,you were my friend,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.66,0:41:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,my ally.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.75,0:41:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You and I have been\Ndestined for one another,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.29,0:42:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,because of your wicked heart
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.66,0:42:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and devilish charm.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.91,0:42:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It was you who pulled me down!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.33,0:42:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Touching me... exciting me...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.12,0:42:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,into this hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.29,0:42:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.83,0:42:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,A black dog bit me, that was you!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.45,0:42:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,His fangs cut me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.29,0:42:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Thorns tore into my flesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.66,0:42:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Those were you too!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.83,0:42:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Th burned like fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.50,0:42:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.70,0:42:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm also the one who saved you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.20,0:42:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Saved me?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.62,0:42:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no need for puny souls\Nwho would throw themselves at my feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.33,0:42:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,My lust hungers for souls
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.54,0:42:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,crushed under the weight of despair,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.33,0:42:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,driven to cursing God, mad for vengeance.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.66,0:42:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yours is coming along quite nicely!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.87,0:43:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, how beautiful you are today.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.25,0:43:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The state of your body, your spirit...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.54,0:43:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That is what stokes my desire\Nand fills me up!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.45,0:43:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.66,0:43:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So they call me.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.41,0:43:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, my wife.\NTell me what you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.45,0:43:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll give you anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.08,0:43:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you want to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.79,0:44:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Something bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.66,0:44:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.12,0:44:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything... so long as it's bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.29,0:44:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Good answer! That's the Jeanne I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.41,0:44:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Now give me your womb, Jeanne,\Nyour soul...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.62,0:44:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And take what I have to give!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.79,0:47:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Spring came around,\Neven to the desolate wilderness.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.70,0:47:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Suddenly Jeanne discovered\Nthat she was not alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.12,0:47:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Nature was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.79,0:47:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You are beautiful, Jeanne.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.66,0:48:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be!\NI thought I had gone to hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.70,0:48:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This is hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.29,0:48:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I gave myself to Satan.\NI should be a wrinkly old witch by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.58,0:48:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,My hair a tangle of\Nvenomous serpents,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.79,0:48:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,my skin green like a toad,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.29,0:48:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,black flames coursing\Nthrough my veins!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.54,0:48:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,This can't be me.\NI'm being deceived!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.75,0:48:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to become a horrifying woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.25,0:48:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I want people to turn away in horror
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.41,0:48:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,when I pass by in the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.87,0:48:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to forget anger and hatred!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.16,0:48:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Who says anger and hatred are ugly?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.70,0:48:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You have become beautiful, Jeanne...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.83,0:48:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.62,0:49:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Like a young girl in love...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.58,0:49:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,radiant.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.87,0:49:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You are even more beautiful than God.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.08,0:49:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Back in the village, it was\Nanother bleak springtime.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.79,0:49:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Jean was back to being\Nan ordinary farmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.45,0:49:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing had changed...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.41,0:49:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,until a dark shadow\Ncrept upon the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.79,0:49:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The black death.\NInfection spelled certain death.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.37,0:54:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Michel, you've noticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.62,0:54:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.66,0:54:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeanne, the witch.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.70,0:54:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh... Where are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.70,0:54:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.29,0:54:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all coming back to me now.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.54,0:54:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I was taken for dead\Nand dumped in the graveyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.12,0:54:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Last I remember\Nis trying to crawl out.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.83,0:54:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't expect to see you\Nin the afterworld.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.62,0:54:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.62,0:54:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.87,0:54:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Liar! That flower's poison!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.16,0:54:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Poison is medicine.\NThat is what cured you.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.66,0:55:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you trying to kill me?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.08,0:55:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you were already dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.33,0:55:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Michel's back from the dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.16,0:55:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He's cured.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.75,0:55:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How did it happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.33,0:55:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Must be a witch!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.62,0:55:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,A witch... A witch...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.20,0:56:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Famine and the plague\Nhave devastated the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.16,0:56:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The surviving villagers\Nmust be starving.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.54,0:56:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet they sing and dance all night
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.83,0:56:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,at that witch's festivities\Nin the wilderness!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.70,0:56:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Magic! Black magic!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.37,0:56:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But it can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.04,0:56:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The villagers bring their\Nown food and drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.08,0:56:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Filthy swines!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.00,0:58:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That woman is still alive?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.62,1:03:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a colorful flower.\NShe extracts juice from it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.16,1:03:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,One sip and my wife's\Nlabor pain went away.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.75,1:03:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If I remember correctly...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.62,1:03:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,"Belladonna, a beautiful woman"
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.04,1:03:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what Jeanne called that flower.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.33,1:03:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We just can't afford to have\Nany more children!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.04,1:03:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.20,1:03:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,My husband wants to every night...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.37,1:03:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel bad to make him suffer.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.45,1:04:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And I get lonely too.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.37,1:04:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So we asked Jeanne if there was a way\Nto do it without making children.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.29,1:04:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh we know it's bad and wrong\Nin God's eyes.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.66,1:04:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an awful sin.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.66,1:04:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But no punishment could be\Nworse than what we've suffered.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.25,1:04:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we're happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.25,1:04:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't regret it,\Nno matter the punishment.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.16,1:04:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to see my grandson,\Nwho died on the battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.12,1:04:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard Jeanne could\Nbring back the dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.25,1:05:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeanne cried her eyes out\Nwhen she heard my story.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.04,1:05:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,She gave me a stick of tobacco
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.29,1:05:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and some blood-red wine to drink.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.08,1:05:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.87,1:05:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Did your dead grandson come back?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.50,1:05:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.58,1:05:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you at least hear his voice?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.08,1:05:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.62,1:05:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you were deceived!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.04,1:05:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I got on my knees crying
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.08,1:05:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and began to pray.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.37,1:05:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,My body was burning up.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.62,1:05:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It all seemed like a dream.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.62,1:05:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I built up my courage\Nand raised my eyes...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.37,1:05:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you see?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.50,1:05:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I could see the host of hellfire
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.50,1:06:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,wailing for my grandson!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.70,1:06:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean to say that satisfied you?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.50,1:06:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yes!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.29,1:06:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never been so happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.58,1:06:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Lord save us all.\NIt's a rebellion against God.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.00,1:06:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,A revolt against you, milord!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.79,1:06:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Seize that woman at once!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.20,1:06:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Burn her at the stake!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.50,1:06:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But the road is rough\Nand the villagers are on her side.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.08,1:06:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,She will run before\Nour soldiers get there.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.83,1:06:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is lord of this land? You? Or...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.20,1:06:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Be patient. We must wait for the\Nenemy to reveal her weakness.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.66,1:06:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave it to me!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.16,1:08:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What ails you, little one?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.45,1:08:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want me?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.66,1:08:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeanne...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.08,1:08:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you recognize me?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.87,1:08:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the Lady's page.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.50,1:08:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,She hates you, so I hated you too.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.37,1:08:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the one who\Nslashed your green cloak.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.58,1:08:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Your point, little page?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.45,1:08:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I did it because...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.54,1:08:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I love her.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.50,1:08:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you here to kill me?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.20,1:08:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I need your help, Jeanne.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.45,1:08:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Hear my plea.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.91,1:08:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to make love to her.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.45,1:08:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.75,1:09:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm only a lowly page.\NShe'd never consider me.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.79,1:09:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Who cares about status?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.91,1:09:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,God granted us our status.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.08,1:09:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Ignoring that is against God!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.29,1:09:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The work of the devil!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.25,1:09:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.12,1:09:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm willing to sell myself\Nto the devil for my love.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.45,1:09:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.41,1:09:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Filthy witch!\NHow dare you!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.16,1:09:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.33,1:09:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll help you.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.45,1:12:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Crafty wench...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.16,1:12:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,She succeeded where\Nthe black death failed
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.08,1:12:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in penetrating the sanctum\Nof the castle.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.29,1:13:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Lord, we must act at once!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.29,1:13:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Call that man!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.00,1:13:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's you...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.79,1:13:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a long time.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.16,1:13:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.58,1:13:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't look happy, Jean.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.33,1:14:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it too late for us?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.79,1:14:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop this madness and come live\Na normal life with me on the farm again.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.08,1:14:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Please forgive me for what I did.\NI had no choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:17.25,1:14:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.08,1:14:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I've forgotten about all that.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.04,1:14:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Come back with me
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.41,1:14:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to the castle.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.45,1:14:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The castle?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.25,1:14:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,His lordship has said\Nhe'll forgive your crimes.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.54,1:14:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only that,\Nhe acknowledges your skills!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:37.00,1:14:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You helped the people\Nget over their suffering.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.25,1:14:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He was in awe of your goodness!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.37,1:14:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And you believe him, Jean.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.58,1:14:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,His lordship says he wants\Nto join forces with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.58,1:14:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What good is your knowledge about\Nhealing herbs and soothing wine,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.83,1:15:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,without the power of the king\Nso it can reach all the land?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.91,1:15:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,His lordship could have sent his troops\Nto capture you or kill you.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.25,1:15:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But he doesn't want that!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.00,1:15:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If you give him all your knowledge,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.87,1:15:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,he promised we could live\Nquietly on a parcel of land.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.41,1:15:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I refuse?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.70,1:15:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll be killed, Jeanne!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.08,1:15:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You... and me both!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.08,1:15:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeanne, please do as I say!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.29,1:17:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't think of this as a trade, Jeanne.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.37,1:17:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of it as a pact\Nbetween you and I,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.41,1:17:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to find a path to lead\Nthe people to happiness!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.41,1:18:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The fertile plot of 100 acres is but\Na humble sign of my goodwill.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.29,1:18:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now please tell the scientists\Nhow to use that strange flower.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.08,1:18:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?\N100 acres not enough?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.45,1:18:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.33,1:18:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,how does the village chief sound?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.25,1:18:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll even make you nobility!\NHow about it?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.70,1:18:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeanne, what are you...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.16,1:18:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine!\NHead of nobility, second only to me!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.04,1:18:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you say?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.66,1:18:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.08,1:18:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't need any of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:48.08,1:18:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh... What on earth do you want, then?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.37,1:18:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.20,1:18:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.79,1:18:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The entire world!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.20,1:19:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,All of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.75,1:19:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare the stake!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.58,1:19:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I want this witch burned\Nat the stake this instant!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.00,1:24:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Jean...
